I’m just getting started and want to tell the app a bit about my health and what I eat, so it can recommend a fitness and meal plan that really fits my needs. ~Lalith Saurabh G

I have some foods I can’t eat (or just really dislike), so I’d love it if the system only suggests meals I’m actually able and willing to try.~Sai Srujan Seelam

My schedule is pretty packed—I need my workouts planned around the days and times I’m actually free, so I can stay on track without stressing out. ~Sai Srujan Seelam

As a vegetarian, I’d like meal plans that help me hit my protein goals without any meat, so I can stay healthy and happy with what I eat.~Lalith Saurabh G

Since I’m new to exercising, I want easy-to-follow routines, with tips for good form and safety reminders, so I don’t risk getting hurt. ~ Shreya Reddy Dubbaka

Because I have a past injury, I want reassurance that my workout won’t include moves that could make it worse—and can be adapted to me. ~Tristan Weingard

Big goals feel overwhelming. I’d appreciate it if the app could break them down into specific steps for each week and day, so I always know exactly what to focus on next.~Tristan Weingard

I’m motivated by seeing progress! I want to be able to check my plans, results, and milestones whenever I want to see how far I’ve come.~Shreya Reddy Dubbaka

Sometimes I get confused or have questions. It would be great to chat with the AI for advice—like why it picked certain foods, or what else I could eat.~Tristan Weingard

My goals and circumstances change, so I want my plans to update too—whenever I hit a milestone or decide to try something new, the app should keep up with me. ~Shreya Reddy Dubbaka
